{
  "texts": [
    "Hyperparameters are configuration settings used to control the learning process and the structure of the model, which are set before the training process begins.",
    "Unlike the model parameters (e.g., weights in a neural network), they are not learned from the data but can significantly impact the model's performance.",
    "Hyperparameter tuning is needed because it helps optimize a machine learning model's performance by finding the best configuration of hyperparameters.",
    "Hyperparameters, set before the training process, significantly affect how well a model learns from data and performs on unseen data.",
    "Proper tuning can lead to better accuracy, faster convergence, and improved generalization, ensuring the model fits the training data well and performs effectively on new, unseen data."
  ]
}